# {name}

{description}

A [dazzlecmd-lib](https://github.com/DazzleTools/dazzlecmd) aggregator: many tools, one command.

## Install (development)

```
pip install -e .
{command} list
```

## Add a tool

Create `{tools_dir}/<namespace>/<tool>/` with a `{manifest}` manifest (or, if you also have dazzlecmd installed, `dz new tool <name>` scaffolds one). Then:

```
{command} list          # discover it
{command} <tool> --help # dispatch it
```

## Layout

```
aggregator.json   # the aggregator's identity (name, command, discovery rules)
{tools_dir}/      # tools, grouped by namespace
kits/             # kit registry pointers (activation control)
src/{name_underscore}/   # the CLI entry point
```
